23/09/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- President Georgi Parvanov and top interior ministry officials met on Monday (22 September) to discuss ways to boost efforts to fight crime and corruption. The sides agreed that existing legislation must be amended. Parvanov then presented their ideas to National Assembly Chairman Ognyan Gerdzhikov.
In other news, Deputy Foreign Minister Ivan Petkov met in Belgrade Monday with his Serbia-Montenegro counterpart, Igor Luksic, and with Serbian Deputy Prime Minister and President of the Co-ordinating Centre for Kosovo Nebojsa Covic. They discussed issues relating to Kosovo, as well as joint economic and infrastructure projects. Bulgaria assumes the OSCE chairmanship in 2004. (BTA, BNT, bTV - 22/09/03)
